=== Dehydration

Dehydration is particularly dangerous given the importance of blood volume for orthostatic tolerance.

Warning signs:

    - Decreased urine output (less than 3–4 voids/day)
    - Dark urine
    - Dry mucous membranes
    - Worsening orthostatic symptoms beyond baseline
    - Tachycardia at rest

Intervention:

    - Increase oral fluids if tolerated
    - Oral rehydration solutions
    - IV fluids if oral rehydration inadequate or not tolerated

